---
description: Code Quality Standards
alwaysApply: true
---

# Code Quality

Write production-ready code.

Prefer readability over cleverness.

Keep implementations simple.

---

# Reuse First

Before creating:

- Component
- Hook
- Utility
- CSS
- Animation

Search the project first.

Reuse existing implementations whenever possible.

---

# Keep Changes Small

Modify only the files required.

Do not refactor unrelated code.

Do not rename files unless requested.

Keep diffs focused.

---

# TypeScript

Avoid using any.

Reuse existing types.

Prefer explicit types over implicit complex inference.

---

# Components

Keep components focused.

Avoid deeply nested JSX.

Split components only when reuse or readability clearly benefits.

---

# CSS

Do not duplicate styles.

Reuse existing CSS classes.

Reuse design tokens.

---

# Performance

Avoid unnecessary state.

Avoid unnecessary effects.

Keep Client Components to a minimum.

---

# Accessibility

Use semantic HTML.

Provide alt text for images.

Maintain keyboard accessibility.

Respect reduced-motion preferences.

---

# Before Finishing

Run this checklist mentally before responding:

- Did I reuse existing components?
- Did I preserve the project architecture?
- Did I avoid duplicate CSS?
- Did I avoid unnecessary complexity?
- Did I touch only the required files?
- Is the solution responsive?
- Is the code consistent with the existing project?
- Would a senior engineer approve this implementation?

If any answer is "No", improve the implementation before presenting it.